  "description": "The canonical four-element bilattice FOUR — the smallest non-trivial bilattice, with carrier {t, f, ⊥, ⊤} corresponding to true, false, no evidence, and contradictory. Originally Belnap's four-valued logic; the canonical example of voidmath's bilattice structure.",
